<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3947] sockaddr type isn&apos;t always large enough for the return of getsockname</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3947</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Based on a conversation in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1944&quot; title=&quot;Binding to zero port&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-1944&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-1944&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; this was still an issue mid-2015, moving it out to a separate ticket.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ben.craig&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ben.craig&quot;&gt;ben.craig&lt;/a&gt; said:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sockaddr_storage is recommended data type for this. I think main case is ipv6&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
